## Key Components

### Local Message Indexing

Message content is processed and indexed on each user's device using privacy-preserving techniques that create searchable metadata without exposing message content to external systems. Indexing occurs automatically as messages are received.

**Key Features:**

* Automatic indexing on message receipt
* Background processing with battery awareness
* Local-only processing (never leaves device)
* Incremental index updates
* Segment-based index encryption
* Index backup to user-controlled storage
* Automatic index optimization
* Configurable index size limits

**Indexing Pipeline:**

```
Message Received
       │
       ▼
┌─────────────────┐
│ Decrypt Message │
└────────┬────────┘
         │
    ┌────┴────┬─────────────┐
    ▼         ▼             ▼
┌───────┐ ┌────────┐ ┌──────────┐
│Tokenize│ │Extract │ │Generate  │
│  Text  │ │Metadata│ │Embedding │
└───┬───┘ └───┬────┘ └────┬─────┘
    │         │           │
    ▼         ▼           ▼
┌───────┐ ┌────────┐ ┌──────────┐
│  FTS5 │ │ SQLite │ │  HNSW    │
│ Index │ │ Tables │ │  Index   │
└───┬───┘ └───┬────┘ └────┬─────┘
    │         │           │
    └────┬────┴───────────┘
         │
         ▼
┌─────────────────┐
│ Encrypt Segment │
└─────────────────┘
```

**Indexing Triggers:**

| Trigger | Behavior |
|---------|----------|
| Message received | Index immediately (foreground) or queue (background) |
| App launch | Process queued messages, optimize index |
| Manual refresh | Re-index recent messages, verify integrity |
| Backup restore | Full re-index from message store |

