### Trust Network Integration

Search results are filtered and ranked based on the sender's trust level and relationship to the searcher.

**Trust-Based Filtering:**

| Filter | Operator | Values |
|--------|----------|--------|
| Trust Level | `trust:` | `unverified`, `newcomer`, `member`, `trusted`, `verified` |
| Circle | `circle:` | `inner`, `trusted`, `known`, `public` |
| Verification | `verified:` | `true`, `false`, `kyc`, `phone`, `email` |
| Relationship | `rel:` | `endorsed`, `endorser`, `mutual`, `blocked` |

**Trust-Based Ranking Boost:**

```typescript
interface TrustRankingConfig {
  // Multiplicative boost by circle
  circleBoost: {
    inner: 1.3;      // +30% relevance
    trusted: 1.15;   // +15% relevance
    known: 1.0;      // baseline
    public: 0.9;     // -10% relevance
  };
  
  // Multiplicative boost by trust level
  trustBoost: {
    verified: 1.2;   // +20% relevance
    trusted: 1.1;    // +10% relevance
    member: 1.0;     // baseline
    newcomer: 0.95;  // -5% relevance
    unverified: 0.85; // -15% relevance
  };
  
  // Additional boosts
  verifiedBadgeBoost: 1.1;    // Has any verification badge
  endorsedByMeBoost: 1.15;    // I endorsed this person
  mutualEndorsementBoost: 1.2; // We endorsed each other
}

function applyTrustBoost(
  results: SearchResult[],
  config: TrustRankingConfig
): SearchResult[] {
  return results.map(result => {
    let boost = 1.0;
    
    // Apply circle boost
    boost *= config.circleBoost[result.senderCircle];
    
    // Apply trust level boost
    boost *= config.trustBoost[result.senderTrustLevel];
    
    // Apply additional boosts
    if (result.senderHasVerification) {
      boost *= config.verifiedBadgeBoost;
    }
    if (result.endorsedByMe) {
      boost *= config.endorsedByMeBoost;
    }
    if (result.mutualEndorsement) {
      boost *= config.mutualEndorsementBoost;
    }
    
    return {
      ...result,
      boostedScore: result.baseScore * boost,
    };
  }).sort((a, b) => b.boostedScore - a.boostedScore);
}
```

**Default Exclusions:**

| Sender Status | Default Behavior | User Override |
|---------------|------------------|---------------|
| Blocked | Excluded from all results | Cannot override |
| Reported as spam | Excluded by default | Can include via filter |
| Trust < 20 | Deprioritized | Can filter to include |
| Public circle | Requires explicit search | Include via `circle:public` |

