### Secure Backup

Archived messages remain fully encrypted and accessible through the search interface. Users can configure secure backup to user-controlled storage locations.

**Key Features:**

* Client-side encryption before upload
* Multiple backup destination support
* Incremental backup (delta sync)
* Backup verification and integrity checks
* Scheduled automatic backups
* Backup versioning and history
* Secure restoration process
* Backup size management

**Backup Destinations:**

| Destination | Encryption | Key Storage | Notes |
|-------------|------------|-------------|-------|
| Local Device | AES-256-GCM | Secure Enclave | External drive, SD card |
| iCloud | AES-256-GCM | Device Keychain | iOS only, encrypted before upload |
| Google Drive | AES-256-GCM | Device Keystore | Android primary, iOS supported |
| IPFS | AES-256-GCM | Device + optional recovery | Decentralized, user-controlled |
| Filecoin | AES-256-GCM | Device + optional recovery | Long-term archival storage |
| Custom S3 | AES-256-GCM | User-managed | Self-hosted option |

**Backup Encryption Flow:**

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    Index Data                           │
└────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────┘
                         │
                         ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              Generate Backup Key                        │
│    backup_key = Argon2id(passkey, backup_salt)         │
└────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────┘
                         │
                         ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              Compress (LZ4)                             │
│    Reduces size 40-60%                                  │
└────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────┘
                         │
                         ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              Encrypt (AES-256-GCM)                      │
│    encrypt(backup_key, compressed_data)                │
└────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────┘
                         │
                         ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              Upload to Destination                      │
│    Only encrypted blob leaves device                    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Backup Metadata (Unencrypted Header):**

```typescript
interface BackupMetadata {
  // Identification
  backupId: string;
  userId: string;          // Hashed, not plaintext
  deviceId: string;        // Hashed
  
  // Versioning
  schemaVersion: number;
  appVersion: string;
  createdAt: Date;
  
  // Size info
  compressedSize: number;
  uncompressedSize: number;
  messageCount: number;    // Approximate, rounded to nearest 1000
  
  // Encryption info
  algorithm: 'AES-256-GCM';
  kdfAlgorithm: 'Argon2id';
  kdfParams: {
    memory: 65536;
    iterations: 3;
    parallelism: 4;
  };
  
