### Cross-Device Search Synchronization

Search indexes can be synchronized across devices while maintaining encryption.

**Key Features:**

* Encrypted index sync between devices
* Delta-based sync (only changes)
* Bandwidth-efficient compression
* Offline search with local index
* Conflict resolution for concurrent edits
* Selective sync by device capability
* Sync progress and status display
* Device authorization management

**Sync Modes:**

| Mode | Index Content | Storage | Use Case |
|------|---------------|---------|----------|
| Full | Complete index | 100% | Primary device |
| Recent | Last 90 days | ~30% | Secondary device |
| Minimal | Last 30 days, no vectors | ~10% | Low-storage device |
| Metadata | Metadata only, fetch on search | ~5% | Temporary device |
| None | No sync | 0% | Privacy-maximum |

**Sync Protocol:**

```typescript
interface SyncProtocol {
  // Device registration
  async registerDevice(deviceInfo: DeviceInfo): Promise<DeviceAuth>;
  async deauthorizeDevice(deviceId: string): Promise<void>;
  
  // Sync operations
  async pushDelta(delta: EncryptedDelta): Promise<SyncResult>;
  async pullDelta(since: SyncCursor): Promise<EncryptedDelta>;
  async resolveConflict(conflict: SyncConflict): Promise<Resolution>;
  
  // Encryption
  keyAgreement: 'X25519';
  bulkEncryption: 'AES-256-GCM';
  
  // Transport
  protocol: 'WebSocket';
  compression: 'LZ4';
  maxDeltaSize: 10 * 1024 * 1024; // 10 MB
}

interface EncryptedDelta {
  deviceId: string;
  sequenceNumber: number;
  timestamp: Date;
  operations: EncryptedBlob;  // Add, update, delete operations
  checksum: string;
}
```

**Conflict Resolution:**

| Conflict Type | Resolution Strategy |
|---------------|---------------------|
| Same message indexed differently | Latest timestamp wins |
| Message deleted on one device | Deletion propagates |
| Archive folder differs | Merge folders, dedupe |
| Settings conflict | Device-specific override |

